{"lemma":"عُذْرَةُ","slug":"عُذْرَةُ","root":"ع.ذ.ر","root_slug":"ع-ذ-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ذ-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28428","n28437","n28438","n28439"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D8%B0%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"virginity"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"excrement, feces"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"an Arab tribe"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28428","headword_ar":"عَذَرَهُ","root":"E*r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orN","text_ar":"عُذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*urN","text_ar":"عُذُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*oraY","text_ar":"عُذْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEo*irapN","text_ar":"مَعْذِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEo*urapN","text_ar":"مَعْذُرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) [all of which are also used as simple substs.]; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AE*rhu","text_ar":"اعذرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He excused him; freed, cleared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exempted, him from blame; exculpated him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he accepted his excuse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"properly,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*arotu","text_ar":"عَذَرْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I cancelled evil conduct."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orN","text_ar":"عُذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*arotuhu fiymaA SanaEa","text_ar":"عَذَرْتُهُ فِيمَا صَنَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I excused,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exculpated, him for what he did."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And in a trad. of El-Mikdád it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hu A_ilayoka","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهُ اـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqado A^aEo*ara","text_ar":"لَقَدْ اَعْذَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"i.e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily God hath excused thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and exempted thee from the obligation to fight against the unbelievers; for he had become extremely fat, and unable to fight. (TA.) And you say [also],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*arahu Eani Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"عَذَرَهُ عَنِ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He excused him for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from, the thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA.) [And accord. to Golius,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*arahu EalaY Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"عَذَرَهُ عَلَى الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"فِى الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but he has not mentioned his authority: see an explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*iyrN","text_ar":"عَذِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from which the former phrase was perhaps derived by him.] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*arotuhu","text_ar":"عَذَرْتُهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino fulaAnK","text_ar":"مِنْ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I excused him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"held him excusable, for his conduct to such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning, I did not blame him, but I blamed such a one. (S, * TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano yaEo*iruniY minohu","text_ar":"مَنْ يَعْذِرُنِى مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Who will excuse me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"make my excuse, if I requite him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for his action,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for his evil action,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and will not blame me"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for it?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who will excuse me with respect to his case, and will not blame me for it?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [And a similar ex. is mentioned in the TA with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY","text_ar":"فِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*ara","text_ar":"عَذَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, S, IKtt, O, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AE*r","text_ar":"اعذر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, IKtt, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iEo*aArN","text_ar":"اـِعْذَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was vitious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faulty, and corrupt:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was guilty of many crimes, sins, faults, offences,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acts of disobedience,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to vender him excusable who punished him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lano yaholika Aln~aAsu Hat~aY yaEo*iruwA","text_ar":"لَنْ يَهْلِكَ النَّاسُ حَتَّى يَعْذِرُوا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino A^anofusihimo","text_ar":"مِنْ اَنْفُسِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, and so in some copies of the S and K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuEo*iruwA","text_ar":"يُعْذِرُوا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in other copies of the S and K, ) both of which readings are the same in meaning, (TA,) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Men will not perish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"die,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until they are guilty of many crimes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sins,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; (S, O, Msb, K;) meaning, (accord. to A 'Obeyd, S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until they deserve punishment, so as to render excusable him who punishes them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, TA.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino nafosihi","text_ar":"مِنْ نَفْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AE*r","text_ar":"اعذر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He placed himself within the power of another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*arotuhu","text_ar":"عَذَرْتُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I aided him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assisted him, against an enemy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*ara","text_ar":"عَذَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*orN","text_ar":"عَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cut off."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA: but only the inf. n. of the verb in this sense is there mentioned.) ―         -b2-  And [hence, probably, as is implied in a passage in the TA, (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orapN","text_ar":"عُذْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*ara","text_ar":"عَذَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, * Msb, K) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*orN","text_ar":"عَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AE*r","text_ar":"اعذر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, Msb, K;) both as expl. by A 'Obeyd; (S;) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He circumcised"},{"kind":"text","text":"a boy, (S, O, Msb, K,) and in like manner a girl; (S, O, Msb;) but when a girl is the object,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xafaDa","text_ar":"خَفَضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is more common. (S, O.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*ara Alfarasa biAlEi*aAri","text_ar":"عَذَرَ الفَرَسَ بِالعِذَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AE*rhu","text_ar":"اعذرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fastened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bound, the horse's"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAr","text_ar":"عِذَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (S, O, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfarasa","text_ar":"الفَرَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AE*r","text_ar":"اعذر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he bridled the horse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alojamahu","text_ar":"اَلْجَمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*arahu","text_ar":"عَذَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E*~rhu","text_ar":"عذّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AE*rhu","text_ar":"اعذرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E*~rhu","text_ar":"عذّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (thus in the TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he put to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAr","text_ar":"عِذَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*arahu","text_ar":"عَذَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*orN","text_ar":"عَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AE*r","text_ar":"اعذر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~ijaAma","text_ar":"اللِّجَامَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he put to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ljAm","text_ar":"لجام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bridle"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bit"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAr","text_ar":"عِذَار"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  And it is said in the Tahdheeb of IKtt that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*arotu Alfarasa","text_ar":"عَذَرْتُ الفَرَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*orN","text_ar":"عَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I cauterized the horse in the place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAr","text_ar":"عِذَار"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b3-  and also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hmlt ElY E*Arh","text_ar":"حملت على عذاره"},{"kind":"text","text":"[an explanation in which there seems to be a mistranscription or an omission, or both; perhaps correctly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalotu EalaY","text_ar":"جَعَلْتُ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfarasi Ei*aArahu","text_ar":"الفَرَسِ عِذَارَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I put upon the horse his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E*Ar","text_ar":"عذار"},{"kind":"text","text":"; a meaning given above]; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEo*arotuhu","text_ar":"اَعْذَرْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dial. var. thereof. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*ira","text_ar":"عُذِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a camel means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was branded with the mark called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAr","text_ar":"عِذَار"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b5-  [Hence, app., the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*arahu","text_ar":"عَذَرَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAll~awomi","text_ar":"بِاللَّوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He branded him with blame;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaTamahu","text_ar":"خَطَمَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bAllwm","text_ar":"باللوم"},{"kind":"text","text":", q.v.]       -A5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*arahu","text_ar":"عَذَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEu*orapu","text_ar":"العُذْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(God, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. a child, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be affected with the pain, in the fauces, termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orap","text_ar":"عُذْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*ira","text_ar":"عُذِرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, affected therewith:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, * TA:) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*orN","text_ar":"عَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orapN","text_ar":"عُذْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IKtt, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","TA","Az","IKtt","God"]},{"entry_id":"n28437","headword_ar":"عُذْرَةٌ","root":"E*r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"virginity, maidenhead,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hymen;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bakaArapN","text_ar":"بَكَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiD~apN","text_ar":"قِضَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so called from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*orN","text_ar":"عَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying the “ act of cutting, ” because a girl's hymen ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAtamu Eu*oratihaA","text_ar":"خَاتَمُ عُذْرَتِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":") is rent when she is devirginated; (Lh, Az, TA;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEu*orapu","text_ar":"العُذْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that whereby a girl is a virgin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA:) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orN","text_ar":"عُذْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"perhaps signifies the same: (see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ariymN","text_ar":"اَرِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and see also the next sentence here following:)] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*arN","text_ar":"عُذَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Devirgination"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a girl [or woman]: (Lh, K:) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orN","text_ar":"عُذْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in the same sense:] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw Eu*orihaA","text_ar":"اَبُو عُذْرِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abw Eu*oratihaA","text_ar":"ابو عُذْرَتِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) (tropical:)  [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the father,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the author, of her devirgination"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one is he who devirginated her."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, K, TA.) And [hence] one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"هٰذَا الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^abuw Ea*ori","text_ar":"هُوَ اَبُو عَذْرِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was the first utterer of this speech"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"هٰذَا الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anota bi*iY Eu*ori","text_ar":"اَنْتَ بِذِى عُذْرِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art not the first utterer of this speech."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA. [But see an assertion of Sb cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iEorN","text_ar":"شِعْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b3-  And The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part in the external organs of generation of a girl or woman termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baZor","text_ar":"بَظْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a girl"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where the operation of circumcision is performed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*orN","text_ar":"عَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying the “ act of cutting. ” (Lh, Az, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaA*uwru","text_ar":"العَاذُورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prepuce"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a boy: (O, K:) so accord. to Lh, who does not say whether it be so called before or after it has been cut off: said by others to be the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion of skin which the circumciser cuts off."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Circumcision;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xitaAnN","text_ar":"خِتَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danaA waqotu Eu*orapi AlS~abiY~i","text_ar":"دَنَا وَقْتُ عُذْرَةِ الصَّبِىِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The time of the circumcision of the boy drew near."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAmapN","text_ar":"عَلَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orN","text_ar":"عُذْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aArN","text_ar":"عِذَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last quarter. ―         -b7-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair upon the withers"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse: (S, O, K:) and, (K,) accord. to As, (S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small quantity, of hair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naASiyap","text_ar":"نَاصِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forelock"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse]; (K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naASiyap","text_ar":"نَاصِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse: (A:) or, accord. to some, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mane"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*arN","text_ar":"عُذَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, TA:) which is said by some to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hairs"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the back of the head to the middle of the neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and, as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orapN","text_ar":"عُذْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sign, mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"token, that is tied to the forelock of a horse that outstrips,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a preservative"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eye."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 795.) ―         -b8-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEu*orapu","text_ar":"العُذْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Five stars at the extremity of the Milky Way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"below Sirius, and also called"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEa*aAraY","text_ar":"العَذَارَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the star e of Canis Major"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which is called by our astronomers “ adara, ” often written “ adard, ”)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with four other neighbouring stars,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which rise"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aurorally"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the midst of the heat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and, (O, K, TA,) as some say, (O, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEu*orapu","text_ar":"العُذْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a star at the time of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"auroral"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rising of which the heat becomes intense;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA;) [app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the star h of Canis Major"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which is called by our astronomers “ aludra ”);]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it rises"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aurorally, in Central Arabia, in the latter part of July O. S.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after Sirius and before Canopus, and is accompanied with intense heat, without wind, taking away the breath."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) ―         -b9-  Also (i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEu*orapu","text_ar":"العُذْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pain in the fauces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arising"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the blood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaA*uwru","text_ar":"العَاذُورُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, accord. to the TA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaAduwraA='u","text_ar":"العَادُورَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (thus in some copies of the K, and thus accord. to the CK;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pain of the fauces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a part near the uvula,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arising"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the blood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) it is said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small swelling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pustule, that comes forth in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarom","text_ar":"خَرْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uvula,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"projection"},{"kind":"text","text":"from the soft palate,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is between the fauces and the nose: it is incident to children, at the time of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"auroral"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rising of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEu*orap","text_ar":"العُذْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the star that rises after Sirius, mentioned above; and on the occasion thereof, a woman has recourse to a piece of rag, which she twists tightly, and inserts into the nose so as to pierce that place, whereupon there issues from it black blood, and sometimes it becomes ulcerated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this piercing is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~agoru","text_ar":"الدَّغْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": then they suspended to the child some such thing as the [amulet termed]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euw*ap","text_ar":"عُوذَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [See 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dgr","text_ar":"دغر"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b10-  It also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The place of the pain above mentioned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is near the uvula."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","Lh","TA","A","O"]},{"entry_id":"n28438","headword_ar":"عِذْرَةٌ","root":"E*r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orN","text_ar":"عُذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places: and see also 8. [Accord. to analogy, it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of excusing."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n28439","headword_ar":"عَذِرَةٌ","root":"E*r","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Human dung"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ordure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * O, * Msb, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaA*irN","text_ar":"عَاذِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, IDrd, O, L, K, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaA*irapN","text_ar":"عَاذِرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K:) pl. of the first [which is the most common]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*iraAtN","text_ar":"عَذِرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and of ↓ the second"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*arN","text_ar":"عُذَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, TA.) ―         -b2-  And hence, (S, O, Msb,) (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"court,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"finaA='","text_ar":"فِنَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a house:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K, TA:) so called because the human ordure ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEa*irap","text_ar":"العَذِرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":") used to be cast in it: (S, O, Msb:) or, accord. to As, this is the primary signification; what is before mentioned being so termed because cast in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fnA'","text_ar":"فناء"},{"kind":"text","text":"; like as it is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAy^iT","text_ar":"غَايِط"},{"kind":"text","text":"because cast in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EAy^T","text_ar":"عايط"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means “ a depressed piece of ground; ” (Har p. 403;) [and] thus says A 'Obeyd: pl. as above: (O, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaA*iru","text_ar":"مَعَاذِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEo*arN","text_ar":"مَعْذَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"which lit. signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place of human dung"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ordure"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*iraAtN","text_ar":"عَذِرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoniyapN","text_ar":"اَفْنِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"finaA='N","text_ar":"فِنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Ham p. 677, q. v.) It is related of 'Alee that he reproved some persons, and said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA lakumo laA tunaZ~ifuwna","text_ar":"مَا لَكُمْ لَا تُنَظِّفُونَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*iraAtikumo","text_ar":"عَذِرَاتِكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * O, TA) i. e. (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What aileth you that ye will not cleanse"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the courts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yards, of your houses?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And in a trad. (O, TA) of the Prophet (O) it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyahuwdu A^anotanu xaloqi A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"اليَهُودُ اَنْتَنُ خَلْقِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*irapF","text_ar":"عَذِرَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, O, TA,) which may mean (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Jews are the most stinking of God's creatures"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of the court,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yard, of the house:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of ordure."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And it is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu labariYo'u AlEa*irapi","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَبَرِىْءُ العَذِرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a phrase like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariYo'u Als~aAHapi","text_ar":"بَرِىْءُ السَّاحَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is clear in respect of the court,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yard, of the house;"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clear of disgrace"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place where people sit"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the court,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yard, of the house."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worst of what come forth from wheat"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corn"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaEaAm","text_ar":"طَعَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (Lh, O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and is thrown away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it is cleared;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*ibapN","text_ar":"عَذِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lh, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["IAar","IDrd","O","L","K","TA","Msb","S","A","Lh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}